THE Imo State House of Assembly has confirmed that lawmakers in the South-East region would give a legal backing to the newly formed Ebube Agu security outfit for the region. Responding to an inquiry from The PUNCH, the Chairman, Committee on Information of the state House of Assembly, Johnson Duru, said the five state houses of Assembly in the region were poised to giving Ebube Agu a legal support. On how it would be achieved, Duru, who represents Ideato South at the state Assembly, said it would be achieved in a joint sitting of all the houses of Assembly in the region. Duru said that the lawmakers from houses of Assembly from Abia, Anambra, Ebonyi, Enugu and Imo states would have a joint session where the legal framework for the takeover of Ebube Agu security outfit would be fine tuned. Responding to an inquiry on whether there will be a joint sitting by the five state houses of Assembly to give Ebube Agu legal support, Duru said, “There is no secrecy. The answer to your question is yes.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com